results.name: Decimal expansion of constant 5 * Pi^2 * A065476 / 48.
link: G. Niklasch, Some number theoretical constants: 1000-digit values. [Cached copy]
mathematica: $MaxExtraPrecision = 500; digits = 98; terms = 500; P[n_] := PrimeZetaP[n] - 1/2^n; LR = Join[{0, 0}, LinearRecurrence[{0, 1, 2}, {-2, -6, -2}, terms + 10]]; r[n_Integer] := LR[[n]];  (5 Pi^2/48)*Exp[NSum[r[n]*P[n - 1]/(n - 1), {n, 3, terms}, NSumTerms -> terms, WorkingPrecision -> digits + 10]] // RealDigits[#, 10, digits]& // First (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Apr 18 2016 *)
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_, Nov 19 2001
